                {
                  q: 'What is the lifespan context manager in FastAPI and why prefer it over @app.on_event?',
                  a: 'The lifespan parameter (3.10+) replaces the deprecated @app.on_event decorator. It uses a single async generator to pair startup and teardown in one block — resources opened before yield are guaranteed to close after yield, even on unexpected shutdown. @app.on_event splits startup and teardown into two unrelated functions with no guaranteed pairing, making cleanup bugs easy to introduce.',
